tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE AB_tests (
  test_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  test_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  test_description TEXT,
  start_date DATE,
  end_date DATE,
  traffic_allocation NUMERIC,
  test_results JSONB
);

CREATE TABLE ab_test_logs (
    test_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    landing_page_url VARCHAR(255),
    user_id INT,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    variation CHAR(1)
);

CREATE TABLE seo_metrics (
    metric_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    landing_page_url VARCHAR(255),
    organic_traffic INT,
    bounce_rate DECIMAL,
    time_on_page INT
);

CREATE TABLE A/B_Test_Results (
    Test_ID INT PRIMARY KEY,
    Test_Name VARCHAR(255),
    Test_Variant VARCHAR(50),
    Test_Start_Date DATE,
    Test_End_Date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE Website_Content (
    Content_ID INT PRIMARY KEY,
    Content_Title VARCHAR(255),
    Content_Text TEXT,
    Content_Type VARCHAR(50),
    Content_URL VARCHAR(255)
);

CREATE TABLE Search_Engine_Rankings (
    Ranking_ID INT PRIMARY KEY,
    Content_ID INT,
    Search_Engine VARCHAR(50),
    Rank_Position INT,
    Rank_Date DATE,
    FOREIGN KEY (Content_ID) REFERENCES Website_Content(Content_ID)
);

CREATE TABLE ab_tests (
  test_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  test_name VARCHAR(255),
  start_date DATE,
  end_date DATE,
  test_description TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE test_variants (
  variant_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  variant_name VARCHAR(255),
  test_id INT,
  variant_description TEXT,
  FOREIGN KEY (test_id) REFERENCES ab_tests(test_id)
);

CREATE TABLE test_results (
  result_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  test_id INT,
  variant_id INT,
  user_id INT,
  conversion BOOLEAN,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP,
  FOREIGN KEY (test_id) REFERENCES ab_tests(test_id),
  FOREIGN KEY (variant_id) REFERENCES test_variants(variant_id)
);

CREATE TABLE user_profile (
  user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  location VARCHAR(255),
  age INT,
  gender VARCHAR(10),
  FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id)
);
